CBOR representation of exchange headers must be canonically-serialized, which means maps must not have multiple entries with the same key.

However, they still can have duplicated HTTP header fields with case differences. For example:
```
[
  {
    ':url': 'https://example.com/'
    ':method': 'GET',
  },
  {
    ':status': '200',
    'Content-Type': ...
    'content-type': ...
  }
]

```
Should the spec explicitly forbid such duplicated headers? Or specify that header names must be stored in lower-case?

