@davidben, you'll probably like this one. It refactors the rules for trusting cross-origin exchanges so that they can be shared by Push and the application/http-exchange format. This let me cover all headers from those two transfer methods unconditionally, with only same-origin exchanges able to use `Signed-Headers` to select a subset.

There's a bunch of text motion, but sections id'ed `signed-headers` and `significant-headers` are basically unchanged in their new locations, and `authority-chain-validation` became the algorithm in `cross-origin-trust`.

